.el .ds Aq '
.TH rom-weaver-ingest 1  "rom-weaver-ingest "
.SH NAME
rom\-weaver\-ingest \- Classify a source as ROM or patch, extracting nested containers and checksumming ROMs
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBrom\-weaver ingest\fR [\fB\-\-json\fR] <\fB\-\-out\-dir\fR> [\fB\-\-progress\fR] [\fB\-\-select\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-progress\fR] [\fB\-\-trace\fR] [\fB\-\-dep\-trace\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-ignore\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-nested\-extract\fR] [\fB\-\-split\-bin\fR] [\fB\-\-checksum\fR] [\fB\-\-threads\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fISOURCE\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Classify a source as ROM or patch, extracting nested containers and checksumming ROMs
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit progress and terminal status as JSON lines
.TP
\fB\-\-out\-dir\fR \fI<DIR>\fR
Directory for extracted ingest outputs
.TP
\fB\-\-progress\fR
Force running progress events on
.TP
\fB\-\-select\fR \fI<SELECT>\fR
Select a payload by exact name, prefix, or glob when an archive carries more than one ROM (repeatable)
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-progress\fR
Disable running progress events
.TP
\fB\-\-trace\fR
Enable trace logs (also enabled by ROM_WEAVER_LOG or RUST_LOG)
.TP
\fB\-\-dep\-trace\fR
Enable trace logs from dependencies (for example nod)
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-ignore\fR
Disable default common\-file ignore filtering during classification and extraction
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-nested\-extract\fR
Do not recursively extract nested containers emitted while ingesting
.TP
\fB\-\-split\-bin\fR [\fI<SPLIT_BIN>\fR]
For a multi\-track CHD CD, force split per\-track BIN (`\-\-split\-bin`/`\-\-split\-bin true`) or a single merged BIN (`\-\-split\-bin false`). Omit to ask the host interactively when the disc offers the choice
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
true
.IP \(bu 2
false
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-checksum\fR \fI<ALGO>\fR
ROM checksum algorithm to compute (repeatable); defaults to crc32, md5, sha1 when omitted
.TP
\fB\-\-threads\fR \fI<auto|N>\fR [default: auto]
Thread budget: auto or a positive integer
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fISOURCE\fR>
Dropped file or container to classify
